        "drawer_M8PnWh": {
          "type": "drawer",
          "settings": {
            "heading": "Delivery & Returns",
            "content_type": "delivery_and_returns",
            "content1": "<p><strong>Delivery</strong><br/><br/><strong>Fast and Reliable</strong><br/><br/>Enjoy fast 1-7 day delivery on all in-stock sofas. delivery with this product. Please note, that orders on finance may take longer when ordering multiple items. </p><p><strong>Real-Time Tracking</strong><br/><br/>Never be left in the dark again! Track your delivery in real-time with our live tracking feature.<br/><br/><strong>Hassle-Free Returns</strong><br/><br/>We offer a 14-day cooling-off period for your peace of mind. If you're not completely satisfied, simply return your item in its original condition within 14 days.</p><p><strong>Need Assistance?</strong><br/><br/>Contact our friendly customer service team for any questions or concerns:</p><p><a href=\"tel:01476 38771\" title=\"tel:01476 38771\">📞 <strong>01476 338771</strong></a><br/><a href=\"mailto:hello@honeypotfurniture.co.uk\" title=\"mailto:hello@honeypotfurniture.co.uk\"><strong>hello@honeypotfurniture.co.uk</strong></a></p><p><strong>Office Hours:</strong><br/><br/>Mon-Fri: 8am-8pm<br/>Sat-Sun: 10am-3pm</p>",
            "content2": "",
            "page": ""
          }
        },
        "drawer_HqH4gX": {
          "type": "drawer",
          "settings": {
            "heading": "Care & Cleaning",
            "content_type": "care_and_cleaning",
            "content1": "<h2>Faux Leather Sofa Care</h2><p>Combatting Spills:</p><ul><li>Act quickly: The sooner you address a spill, the easier it will be to remove.</li><li>Blot, don't rub: Use a clean, absorbent cloth to blot up the spill. Rubbing can spread the stain.</li><li>Avoid harsh chemicals: Strong cleaners can damage the faux leather. Opt for mild, leather-safe products.</li><li>For stubborn stains: If the spill is persistent, consult a professional cleaning service.</li></ul><p>General Cleaning Tips:</p><ul><li>Regular dusting: Use a soft brush or duster to remove dust and debris.</li><li>Weekly wipe-down: With a damp, soft cloth and a mild leather cleaner, gently wipe down the surface.</li><li>Avoid direct sunlight: Prolonged exposure to sunlight can cause fading and drying.</li><li>Protect from moisture: Excessive moisture can lead to mold and mildew.</li></ul><p>Additional Tips:</p><ul><li>Prevent stains: Use protective covers or throws when eating or drinking on your sofa.</li><li>Handle pets carefully: If you have pets, keep them off the sofa or use pet-friendly covers.</li><li>Avoid sharp objects: Be cautious of sharp items that could scratch the surface.</li></ul><p>By following these tips, you can keep your faux leather sofa looking its best for years to come.</p>",
            "content2": "<h2>Fabric Sofa Care</h2><p>Spills:</p><ul><li>Act quickly: The sooner you address a spill, the easier it will be to remove.</li><li>Blot, don't rub: Use a clean, absorbent cloth to blot up the spill. Rubbing can spread the stain.</li><li>Avoid harsh chemicals: Strong cleaners can damage the fabric. Opt for mild, fabric-safe products.</li><li>For stubborn stains: If the spill is persistent, consult a professional cleaning service.</li></ul><p>General Cleaning:</p><ul><li>Regular vacuuming: Vacuum your sofa regularly to remove dust and dirt.</li><li>Spot cleaning: For stains or spills, use a mild upholstery cleaner and a clean, soft cloth. Test the cleaner in an inconspicuous area first to ensure it doesn't cause discoloration.</li><li>Avoid excessive moisture: While spot cleaning is necessary, avoid soaking the fabric. Too much moisture can lead to mold or mildew.</li></ul><p>Protection:</p><ul><li>Protect from sunlight: Prolonged exposure to direct sunlight can cause fading. Consider using curtains or blinds to protect your sofa.</li><li>Prevent moisture: Keep your sofa away from damp areas and avoid placing it directly on the floor. Consider using a sofa cover or throw to protect it from spills and wear and tear.</li></ul><p>Conditioning:</p><ul><li>Use fabric conditioner or protector: To help maintain the fabric's appearance and durability, apply a fabric conditioner or protector according to the manufacturer's instructions.</li></ul><p>Prevention:</p><ul><li>Use covers: To protect your sofa from spills, stains, and wear and tear, consider using removable covers.</li><li>Handle pets carefully: If you have pets, keep them off the sofa or use pet-friendly covers to prevent damage.</li><li>Avoid sharp objects: Be cautious of sharp items that could snag or tear the fabric.</li></ul><p>By following these tips, you can keep your fabric sofa looking its best for years to come.</p>",
            "page": ""
          }
        },
